From: 4noha
Subject: if_bwfm_sdio: guard bwfm_sdio_task against half-initialized softc on resume
License: ISC (this patch modifies OpenBSD source and inherits ISC; see ../LICENSE-ISC)

if_bwfm_sdio: guard bwfm_sdio_task against half-initialized softc on resume.

Problem (2026-06-02..03, DM250 / rk3128):
  After applying dwmmc-resume-pwrseq.diff the resume-time chip
  power-cycle was working and the original error 60 (ETIMEDOUT) was
  gone. But on the re-attach window bwfm_sdio_task could run from systq
  while the softc was still being initialised (sc->sc_lock == NULL) —
  NULL deref -> kernel data abort. ddb trace:
    bwfm_sdio_task -> taskq_thread.

Fix:
  1. Early-return from bwfm_sdio_task() when sc->sc_lock is unset.
     (Filters out a task that fired between softc allocation and the
     attach path setting sc_lock.)
  2. In bwfm_sdio_detach(), call taskq_barrier(systq) after task_del
     so any in-flight task that already passed the NULL guard drains
     before detach proceeds.

Target: sys/dev/sdmmc/if_bwfm_sdio.c.

CAUTION: this patch DOES NOT resolve the resume crash by itself. It
eliminates one class of fault (error 60 + sc_task NULL deref) but in
testing the crash moved to a later layer (see
ieee80211-media-status-nullguard.diff and bwfm-suspend-down.diff).
Retained in the stack as scaffolding for further work and so the v2
working kernel can be rebuilt.

--- sys/dev/sdmmc/if_bwfm_sdio.c.orig
+++ sys/dev/sdmmc/if_bwfm_sdio.c
@@ bwfm_sdio_task(void *arg) @@
 	struct bwfm_sdio_softc *sc = arg;
 	uint32_t clkctl, devctl, intstat, hostint;
+
+	/*
+	 * On resume the chip is power-cycled and bwfm re-attaches; the softc
+	 * may not be fully initialized yet when this task fires from systq.
+	 * Touching sc->sc_lock (and everything it guards) before init would
+	 * fault.  Bail out until the attach path has set sc_lock.
+	 */
+	if (sc->sc_lock == NULL)
+		return;

 	rw_enter_write(&sc->sc_lock);

@@ bwfm_sdio_detach(struct device *self, int flags) @@
 	task_del(systq, &sc->sc_task);
+	taskq_barrier(systq);	/* wait for an in-flight sc_task to drain */

 	bwfm_detach(&sc->sc_sc, flags);

Notes:
  - sc_lock type is `struct rwlock`. Comparing against NULL works as a
    cheap "before rw_init" check; a dedicated "ready" flag would be
    cleaner.
  - taskq_barrier(systq) is called from detach (process context); OK.
  - Upstream (jcs rk3128 / OpenBSD) does not yet implement bwfm
    DVACT_SUSPEND/RESUME that takes net80211 nodes / BA timers down,
    which is needed for a real fix (see bwfm-suspend-down.diff for the
    v3 approach that actually works without firmware I/O on QUIESCE).
